<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4853#p4853</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4853#p4853"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Joypad D1]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4853#p4853"><![CDATA[
On the NES, $4016.1 and $4017.1 have data if you have connected an adapter to the expansion port. In fact, this could be used as an adapter to make up to 8 players: one Four Score connected to $4016.0 and $4017.0 and one Four Score connected to $4016.1 and $4017.1.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Sep 24, 2005 1:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
