<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Quietust]]></name></author>
<updated>2005-09-24T09:38:32-07:00</updated>
<published>2005-09-24T09:38:32-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4844#p4844</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4844#p4844"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Joypad D1]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=594&amp;p=4844#p4844"><![CDATA[
D1 is used on the Famicom <strong>only</strong> in order to check controllers connected to the expansion port; many games released in the USA simply did not have this logic removed (since it did not cause any problems).<br /><br />This is the same reason why most licensed Zapper/PowerPad games only allow said peripheral to be connected to the <strong>second</strong> controller port - on the Famicom they were connected to the expansion port, which connected them to the bits in $4017 only.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Sat Sep 24, 2005 9:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
